main event: On May 30, 1964, a brilliant bluish-white object was observed in the sky in the Far East.
interesting points: The object was much larger than a first magnitude star., The object appeared to be flying at a high speed and disappeared behind trees., The sighting was recorded by Coral 30/17252., The object was observed from a course of GGO degrees at an azimuth of 25 degrees., The report suggests that the most probable explanation for the appearance was a meteor.
